title: Indonesia Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Indonesia Three Month Interbank Rate was at 5.68 percent on Monday November 7. Interbank Rate in Indonesia averaged 10.94 percent from 1996 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 57.79 percent in September of 1998 and a record low of 3.75 percent in April of 2022. In Indonesia, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Indonesia Interbank Call Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Bank Indonesia
